{"kind":"article","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/tuikit\/focussystem"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"TUIkit provides a focus system that lets users move between interactive views (buttons, menus, text fields) using Tab, Shift+Tab, or arrow keys. The system consists of three parts:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FocusManager"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Tracks which element is focused, handles navigation"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/Focusable","type":"reference"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Protocol that views adopt to receive focus"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/FocusState"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Lightweight state object that views use to query and request focus"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"How Focus Works","anchor":"How-Focus-Works"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Every frame, the ","type":"text"},{"code":"FocusManager","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is cleared and interactive views re-register themselves during rendering. This means focus registrations are always in sync with the current view tree: removed views are automatically unregistered.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The focus order follows the rendering order: the first focusable view rendered is first in the Tab cycle."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"The Focusable Protocol","anchor":"The-Focusable-Protocol"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Views that want to receive focus conform to ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/Focusable","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":":","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["public protocol Focusable: AnyObject {","    var focusID: String { get }","    var canBeFocused: Bool { get }","    func onFocusReceived()","    func onFocusLost()","    func handleKeyEvent(_ event: KeyEvent) -> Bool","}"]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"code":"focusID","type":"codeVoice"}]},{"text":": Unique identifier for this focusable element","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"canBeFocused"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Whether focus can move to this element (default: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":")"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"code":"onFocusReceived()","type":"codeVoice"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Called when this element gains focus (default: no-op)"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"code":"onFocusLost()","type":"codeVoice"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Called when this element loses focus (default: no-op)"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"handleKeyEvent(_:)","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": Handle a key event while focused; return ","type":"text"},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" if consumed","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A default extension provides sensible defaults for ","type":"text"},{"code":"canBeFocused","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" (","type":"text"},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"), ","type":"text"},{"code":"onFocusReceived()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", and ","type":"text"},{"code":"onFocusLost()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" (both no-ops). Only ","type":"text"},{"code":"focusID","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"handleKeyEvent(_:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" must be implemented.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Using FocusState","anchor":"Using-FocusState"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/FocusState","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" is the user-facing API for checking and requesting focus inside a view:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let focusState = FocusState(id: \"my-button\", focusManager: context.environment.focusManager)","","\/\/ Check if this element is currently focused","if focusState.isFocused {","    \/\/ render with focus indicator","}","","\/\/ Programmatically request focus","focusState.requestFocus()"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Built-in views like ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/Button","type":"reference"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/Menu","type":"reference"},{"text":" create their own ","type":"text"},{"code":"FocusState","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" internally: you only need it when building custom focusable views.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Navigation Keys","anchor":"Navigation-Keys"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"FocusManager","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" responds to these keys during dispatch:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"table","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Key"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Action"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Tab","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Move focus to the next element","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Shift+Tab","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Move focus to the previous element","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Arrow Down \/ Right"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Move focus to the next element"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Arrow Up \/ Left"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Move focus to the previous element","type":"text"}]}]]],"header":"row"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"FocusRegistration Helper","anchor":"FocusRegistration-Helper"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Built-in interactive views use the internal "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FocusRegistration"},{"type":"text","text":" helper to avoid boilerplate. It handles three tasks in one call:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Persist a focus ID","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" via "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"StateStorage"},{"type":"text","text":" so it remains stable across renders"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Register","type":"text"}]},{"text":" the handler with the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FocusManager"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Query"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" whether this view currently has focus","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Custom views that implement "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/Focusable"},{"type":"text","text":" typically do not need "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FocusRegistration"},{"type":"text","text":" directly. It is used by the framework’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"_*Core"},{"type":"text","text":" views (e.g. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"_ButtonCore"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"_ListCore"},{"type":"text","text":")."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Focus Indicator","anchor":"Focus-Indicator"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The visual indicator depends on the view type. Buttons and similar controls use a ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"highlight background bar"}]},{"text":" for the focused item. Text fields use ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"pulsing vertical bars"}]},{"text":" (caps) around the input area. Lists and tables use a ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"highlight background","type":"text"}]},{"text":" for the focused row, with a ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"pulsing accent background"}]},{"text":" when the row is both focused and selected.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Focus in the Event Loop","anchor":"Focus-in-the-Event-Loop"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Focus dispatch happens in Layer 2 of the key event pipeline (see "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/AppLifecycle","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"):"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A key event arrives from stdin"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Layer 1 (status bar) gets first chance to handle it"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Layer 2: ","type":"text"},{"code":"KeyEventDispatcher","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" dispatches to the focused view’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"handleKeyEvent(_:)","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If not consumed, navigation keys (Tab, arrows) are handled by "},{"code":"FocusManager","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Layer 3 (default bindings) handles quit, theme cycling, etc.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Navigate between interactive elements using the keyboard."}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Guides","anchor":"Guides","identifiers":["doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/StateManagement","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/ThemingGuide","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/StatusBarGuide","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/AppearanceAndColors","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/Preferences","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/CustomViews","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/KeyboardShortcuts","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/PaletteReference","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/ListAndTable","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/LayoutSystem"]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/FocusSystem","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"title":"Focus System","roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"TUIkit"}],"role":"article"},"references":{"doc://TUIkit/documentation/TUIkit/Menu":{"title":"Menu","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/tuikit\/menu","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/Menu","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"A vertical menu displaying a list of selectable items.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Menu","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Menu","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://TUIkit/documentation/TUIkit/AppLifecycle":{"url":"\/documentation\/tuikit\/applifecycle","role":"article","title":"App Lifecycle","abstract":[{"text":"Understand how a TUIkit a